NAME
orpgdat_api - ORPG Library Data Attribute Table (DAT) access routines

SYNOPSIS

#include <orpg.h>

void ORPGDAT_error(void (*user_exception_callback)());
int ORPGDAT_read_tbl();
Mrpg_data_t* ORPGDAT_get_entry (int data_id, int *size);
Mrpg_wp_item* ORPGDAT_get_write_permission(int data_id, int *size);
int ORPGDAT_get_compression_type (int data_id);


OVERVIEW
The functions are described separately below.

NAME
ORPGDAT_error() - This function registers a call back function, which    
                  will be called when an exception condition is  
                  encountered. 

SYNOPSIS
#include <orpg.h>

int ORPGDAT_error(void(*user_exception_callback)())

DESCRIPTION
This function registers a user-defined callback function, which is
called whenever there is a exception condition.

RETURNS
There is no return value defined for this function.

NAME
ORPGDAT_read_tbl() - reads the data attributes table from LB into 
                     internal buffer

SYNOPSIS
#include <orpg.h>

int ORPGDAT_read_tbl()

DESCRIPTION
This functions reads all entries in the data attributes table and stores
this information in internal memory on behalf of the other API functions.

RETURNS
This function returns 0 is the read was successful or a negative error
code if the read failed.


NAME
ORPGDAT_get_entry(int data_id, int *size) - returns the data attributes table 
entry associated with data_id.

SYNOPSIS
#include <orpg.h>

Mrpg_data_t* ORPGDAT_get_entry(int data_id, int *size);

DESCRIPTION
This function returns the data attributes entry associated with "data_id".  The
size of the entry is returned in "size".

RETURNS
ORPGDAT_get_entry returns pointer to Mrpg_data_t structure or NULL if no entry 
is found.  NOTE:  User is responsible for freeing memory associated with entry.

NAME
ORPGDAT_get_write_permission(int data_id, int *size) - returns the write permission 
table associated with data_id.

SYNOPSIS
#include <orpg.h>

Mrpg_wp_item* ORPGDAT_get_write_permission(int data_id, int *size);

DESCRIPTION
This function returns the data attributes write permission table associated with
"data_id".  The size of the table is returned in "size".

RETURNS
ORPGDAT_get_write_permission returns pointer to Mrpg_wp_item structure or NULL
if no entry is found.  NOTE:  User is responsible for freeing memory associated
with entry.

NAME
ORPGDAT_get_compression_type(int data_id) - returns the compression code 
associated with data_id.

SYNOPSIS
#include <orpg.h>

int ORPGDAT_get_compression_type(int data_id);

DESCRIPTION
This function returns the compression code associated with "data_id".  

RETURNS
ORPGDAT_get_compression_type returns compression code associated with "data_id".
If no entry is found, a negative error code is returned.  

